
[1]afeard

   AFE'ARD, a. Afeard is the participle passive. See Fear.]

   Afraid; affected with fear or apprehension, in a more moderate degree
   than is expressed by terrified. It is followed by of, but no longer
   used in books, and even in popular use, is deemed vulgar.
